{
  "stem": "3022.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before I hooked up with my friend Oscar, I remember an incident which was of some importance, because it catalogs my first encounter with Jewish women after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the 8th of May, Germany formally surrendered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And General Eisenhower had proclamations in German and in English on all the buildings in the cities and villages.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went to the town of Eggenfelden to read those proclamations.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And somebody mentioned, in the course of conversation with some of the survivors, that he heard that in the village of Simbach, somebody saw some Jewish women.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That night when we returned back to the farm where we were staying, the conversation revolved around the Jewish women.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As I said, the hope against hope was maybe, maybe these women are women that our kin, our relatives, or maybe they know they were at camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And other woman, maybe they know where our relatives are.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the decision was made-- despite the fact that we were physically run down-- that we will go and try to find out what is to be found out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So myself and two other fellows, younger fellows, we got together many of the things that the black GIs dropped off-- from the K-rations, C-rations, cigarettes, canned food, SPAM, God forbid, and whatever there was, cheese.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we took with us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we got a lift from an American, from two American soldiers that were going in the Jeep in that direction.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They dropped us off about 10 miles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave us a lift, and we went on foot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we got very tired, so we hired a German farmer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we gave him all our cigarettes for taking us to the town of Simbach.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we arrived in Simbach, we asked, are there any women inmates?",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
